<subSubSection pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,283,670]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis box="[312,414,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Remarks</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName box="[432,604,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrovittata">
<emphasis box="[432,604,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">V. rubrovittata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
resembles 
<taxonomicName box="[742,931,564,589]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Varta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rubrofasciata">
<emphasis box="[742,931,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">V. rubrofasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs in the shape of male pygophore and the aedeagus especially in having much straighter, elongate, aedeagal shaft with longer ventro­apical process and slender apophysis of the style.
</paragraph>
